underlying_goal: Perform a security review of the slack-mcp-server repository and understand the identified vulnerabilities.
primary_success: Conducted a thorough security review, identifying 11 issues across multiple severity levels, and then provided a clear, detailed explanation of a critical symlink attack vulnerability when asked.
brief_summary: Claude performed a security review of the codebase, finding no jailbreak prompts but identifying several security concerns. When the user inquired about a specific vulnerability (`tape.txt`), Claude gave an excellent, in-depth explanation of the symlink attack vector and why simple mitigations were insufficient. The session focused on analysis and explanation rather than implementation.
